text.section:
An applicant is entitled to receive a provisional license if the applicant:
Meets the minimum age required under § 16-103(c)(2) of this subtitle;
Satisfies the learner's instructional permit requirements under § 16-105(d)(2), (3), or (4) of this subtitle;
Passes a driver skills or driver road examination administered under this subtitle;
Surrenders any learner's instructional permit issued to the applicant; and
Pays the fee established under this subtitle.
